(1290, 1, '2016-07-12 07:03:10', '2016-07-12 11:03:10', 'Suite à l''annonce de la <a href="http://maniacdesports.com/2016/07/11/officiel-le-ufc-vendu-pour-4g/">vente du UFC</a> pour 4G$ de dollars au consortium mené par William Morris et IMG, de nombreux combattants ont réagi sur twitter.\n\nPlusieurs, dont Conor McGregor, se sont montrés heureux et reconnaissants:\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-lang="en">\n<p dir="ltr" lang="en">I am honoured to have fought under the Fertitta regime! To have been mentored by these great people on this great business is a true honour!</p>\n— Conor McGregor (@TheNotoriousMMA) <a href="https://twitter.com/TheNotoriousMMA/status/752400278117183489">July 11, 2016</a></blockquote>\n<script src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" async="" charset="utf-8"></script>\n\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-lang="en">\nIm excited to see the global expansion by the new <a href="https://twitter.com/ufc">@ufc</a> team! Big things coming! Hopefully a few new <a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/wmma?src=hash">#wmma</a> weight classes too! I''m ready\n\n— Cris Cyborg (@criscyborg) <a href="https://twitter.com/criscyborg/status/752529251228749824">July 11, 2016</a>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-lang="en">\nGot a new boss, <a href="https://twitter.com/ufc">@ufc</a> new PR machine, here comes <a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/bigcountry?src=hash">#bigcountry</a> pushed to a new level. <a href="https://t.co/HLYuXDQb1x">https://t.co/HLYuXDQb1x</a>\n\n— Roy Nelson (@roynelsonmma) <a href="https://twitter.com/roynelsonmma/status/752536298364166144">July 11, 2016</a>\n</blockquote>\n\n<script src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" async="" charset="utf-8"></script>\n\n<script src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" async="" charset="utf-8"></script>\n\nJosh Samman a noté que le UFC avait été vendu au même prix que Disney a payé pour la franchise Star Wars:\n\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-lang="en">\nUFC worth as much as Star Wars. Pretty damn crazy.\n\n— Josh Samman (@JoshSamman) <a href="https://twitter.com/JoshSamman/status/752509811338665984">July 11, 2016</a>\n</blockquote>\n\n<script src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" async="" charset="utf-8"></script>\n\nPlusieurs voient dans cette vente la possibilité d''améliorer les conditions des combattants:\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-lang="en">\n<p dir="ltr" lang="en">1 single move that would change the sport for the best, literally overnight..\n\nMatch the revenue split to all major sports. (Close to 50/50)</p>\n— Johnny Hollywood (@HollywoodCase) <a href="https://twitter.com/HollywoodCase/status/752534545052819456">July 11, 2016</a></blockquote>\n<script src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" async="" charset="utf-8"></script>\n\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-lang="en">\nPerfect time to change the revenue split to ➡️ 46% / 54% split to be equal to the other major sports.💰💰💰 <a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/WeAllNeedToEat?src=hash">#WeAllNeedToEat</a>\n\n— Jeremy Stephens (@LiLHeathenMMA) <a href="https://twitter.com/LiLHeathenMMA/status/752376203881746436">July 11, 2016</a>\n</blockquote>\n\n<script src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" async="" charset="utf-8"></script>\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-lang="en">\n<p dir="ltr" lang="en">4 bil... I was probably worth more and so was everyone else right?</p>\n— Al Iaquinta (@ALIAQUINTA) <a href="https://twitter.com/ALIAQUINTA/status/752501475125895168">July 11, 2016</a></blockquote>\n<script src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" async="" charset="utf-8"></script>\n\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-lang="en">\nSo I asked UFC brass after the sale, does that mean we all get paid more??? and they said... <a href="https://t.co/vaRoSPz35X">https://t.co/vaRoSPz35X</a>\n\n— Big Ben Rothwell (@RothwellFighter) <a href="https://twitter.com/RothwellFighter/status/752541463745929216">July 11, 2016</a>\n</blockquote>\n\n<script src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" async="" charset="utf-8"></script>\n\nÀ l''inverse, Joe Ellenberger a félicité les anciens actionnaires pour leur excellent investissement:\n\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-lang="en"><p lang="en" dir="ltr">Congrats on the great investment years ago <a href="https://twitter.com/danawhite">@danawhite</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/lorenzofertitta">@lorenzofertitta</a> Looking forward to seeing the <a href="https://twitter.com/ufc">@ufc</a> grow even more!</p>&mdash; Joe Ellenberger (@JoeEllenberger) <a href="https://twitter.com/JoeEllenberger/status/752495898421178370">July 11, 2016</a></blockquote>\n<script async src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script>\n\nPlus tôt aujourd''hui, une lettre a été envoyée à tous les combattants pour les informer du changement de propriétaire, confirmant du même coup que les Fertitta et Dana White allaient tout de même continuer à faire partie de la compagnie.\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-lang="en">That makes it official. <a href="https://t.co/whBUODcXaP">https://t.co/whBUODcXaP</a><a href="https://t.co/C0liWVOpqD">pic.twitter.com/C0liWVOpqD</a>\n\n— Joe Lauzon (@JoeLauzon) <a href="https://twitter.com/JoeLauzon/status/752485836822839296">July 11, 2016</a></blockquote>\nSource: <a href="http://www.foxsports.com/ufc/story/conor-mcgregor-ufc-fighters-react-to-4-billion-sale-071116">Fox Sports</a>\n\n<script src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" async="" charset="utf-8"></script>', 'Les réactions des combattants à la vente du UFC.', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'les-reactions-des-combattants-a-la-vente-du-ufc', '', '', '2016-07-12 07:03:10', '2016-07-12 11:03:10', '', 0, 'http://maniacdesports.com/?p=1290', 0, 'post', '', 0),
